results.name: Number of unlabeled connected planar graphs with n edges with degree >= 3 at each node.
link: Hugo Pfoertner, Illustrations of terms a(9) - a(11).
example: a(6) = 1: the 3-connected edge graph of the tetrahedron;
a(7) = 0: no connected planar graph with degree >=3 at each node exists;
a(8) = 1: the 3-connected 5-wheel graph, edge graph of 4-sided pyramid;
